- Agent should always run Python code in a virtual environment
- Required packages should always be installed in the virtual environment
- Activate the virtual environment using `.\.venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1` (PowerShell) or `.\.venv\Scripts\activate` (Command Prompt)
- Create virtual environment with `python -m venv .venv` if it doesn't exist
- Always use `pip install` within the activated virtual environment
- Verify virtual environment is active before running any Python commands
- Include requirements.txt file for dependency management
- Use specific package versions in requirements.txt when possible
- Deactivate virtual environment with `deactivate` when done
- Never install packages globally when working on projects